02:59.167 --> 03:01.433
Oman defies expectations.

03:04.200 --> 03:05.500
It shouldn't... according to

03:05.533 --> 03:08.533
the cruel logic
of the world... exist.

03:08.567 --> 03:11.667
But it does,
and it's incredible.

03:19.600 --> 03:23.800
The sultanate of Oman
is an absolute monarchy,

03:23.833 --> 03:25.633
a predominantly Islamic state

03:25.667 --> 03:27.833
and a vital strategic
choke point

03:27.867 --> 03:30.067
in the world's oil supply.

03:33.800 --> 03:35.700
It is surrounded by some of
the trickiest

03:35.733 --> 03:40.333
and most contentious powers
in the region.

03:40.367 --> 03:44.033
And yet, here it is,
relatively small,

03:44.067 --> 03:46.333
tolerant,
welcoming to outsiders,

03:46.367 --> 03:50.700
peaceful,
and stunningly beautiful.

03:50.733 --> 03:53.500
But Oman is facing uncertainty
with succession issues

03:53.533 --> 03:55.767
and declining oil reserves.

03:55.800 --> 03:58.800
The question of what's next
is a big,

03:58.833 --> 04:00.767
if often unspoken one.

04:03.667 --> 04:06.200
So, pre-1970,
this was a very different,

04:06.233 --> 04:07.700
very different place to live.

04:07.733 --> 04:08.900
Very different country.

04:08.933 --> 04:10.767
Quite simply, there was nothing.

04:10.800 --> 04:13.833
We had only three schools
all over Oman.

04:13.867 --> 04:15.333
And only for boys.

04:15.367 --> 04:17.367
We had only two hospitals.

04:17.399 --> 04:19.567
- For the whole country.
- Yes, for the whole country.

04:19.600 --> 04:23.800
And nine miles of paved road
in Muscat.

04:23.833 --> 04:27.400
And what happened outside of
Muscat was really of no concern

04:27.433 --> 04:30.967
to leadership.
Absolutely, yes.

04:35.667 --> 04:37.533
Sheikh Zayed bin
Sulaiman al-Ghafri

04:37.567 --> 04:41.433
is a businessman
and the son of a tribal leader.

04:41.467 --> 04:44.100
He's the kind of guy who will
likely be prominent

04:44.133 --> 04:46.667
in the future of the country.

04:46.700 --> 04:49.500
The current Sultan
replaced his father

04:49.533 --> 04:54.433
and took the country, really,
from the 19th century

04:54.467 --> 04:58.733
into the 20th century
very, very quickly.

04:58.767 --> 05:00.433
Absolutely.
His Majesty took over

05:00.467 --> 05:04.133
and he changed the whole scene.

05:04.167 --> 05:06.200
This is not a democracy.

05:06.233 --> 05:08.433
But everybody, everybody,
it seems,

05:08.467 --> 05:12.967
has genuine affection
and respect for the Sultan.

05:17.067 --> 05:20.767
Sultan Qaboos bin Said
al Said is the much-admired

05:20.800 --> 05:24.133
and enigmatic absolute ruler
and monarch.

05:24.167 --> 05:28.567
He's presided over everything
Omani for the last 47 years.

05:28.600 --> 05:31.267
In that time, he's raised
a nation... literally...

05:31.300 --> 05:33.500
From a dusty,
primitive backwater

05:33.533 --> 05:38.333
to a modern, functioning,
largely secular society.

05:38.367 --> 05:41.633
His vision was to deliver
the surfaces first.

05:41.667 --> 05:46.733
Electricity, water,
heath care, education.

05:46.767 --> 05:48.733
It was like a one man show.

05:48.767 --> 05:51.367
And usually, one man shows
are not a good thing.

05:51.400 --> 05:52.967
- That's right.
- I mean, historically,

05:53.000 --> 05:54.767
seldom does that work out.

05:54.800 --> 05:56.533
But, you know, you look around
and see how

05:56.567 --> 05:59.267
the county's doing now,
it's pretty impressive.

05:59.300 --> 06:03.333
It's a tremendous job
that His Majesty has done.

06:03.367 --> 06:05.400
People just felt like
he's the man

06:05.433 --> 06:08.867
that they were waiting for
to enlight their life.

06:08.900 --> 06:10.300
And to open doors for them.

06:15.467 --> 06:15.967
♪

06:21.667 --> 06:23.367
Oman, it should be understood,

06:23.400 --> 06:26.400
sits at the top
of the Indian Ocean rim.

06:26.433 --> 06:30.400
The empire once stretched
from Pakistan to East Africa,

06:30.433 --> 06:32.100
with important trade routes
that reached

06:32.133 --> 06:35.133
from southern Africa all
the way to the China Straits,

06:35.167 --> 06:39.167
Indonesia and deep into
East Asia.

06:39.200 --> 06:41.767
Modern Oman is a fraction
of that size now.

06:41.800 --> 06:46.133
But its DNA, its culture,
cuisine... and to some extent...

06:46.167 --> 06:48.100
Attitude toward
the outside world

06:48.133 --> 06:50.500
is a reflection of that history.

06:53.267 --> 06:56.333
Muttrah is a port town
in the capital of Muscat.

06:56.367 --> 07:00.233
For centuries, a central hub
of commerce and trade.

07:00.267 --> 07:02.500
One of the first things
I noticed about the city

07:02.533 --> 07:04.733
is it's very low slung.
Yeah.

07:04.767 --> 07:09.233
It seems like a calculated,
aesthetic decision.

07:09.267 --> 07:10.760
If you're someone who wants
to build your house,

07:10.767 --> 07:13.567
you first submit your plans
to municipality.

07:13.600 --> 07:15.367
And if you're going above
a certain height,

07:15.400 --> 07:16.800
it's generally frowned upon.

07:16.833 --> 07:18.267
'Cause the idea is to keep

07:18.300 --> 07:22.133
a sort of traditional
Omani vernacular.

07:22.167 --> 07:25.100
Aisha Stoby is a curator
and PhD student

07:25.133 --> 07:27.367
focused on Middle Eastern
art history.

07:27.400 --> 07:29.567
She is,
like many young people here,

07:29.600 --> 07:33.400
patriotic to the point of being
nerdy, as she puts it.

07:33.433 --> 07:35.067
We have such an old history.

07:35.100 --> 07:38.400
And I think Muttrah is a really
great example of that, you know?

07:38.433 --> 07:40.733
This is something that
functions in our daily life.

07:40.767 --> 07:43.300
It functions very similarly to,
say, how it would've functioned

07:43.333 --> 07:46.100
if you were coming into Muttrah
and going into the Souq,

07:46.133 --> 07:48.333
say, 200 years ago.

07:48.367 --> 07:50.867
And now we're coming
to the Corniche, which is...

07:50.900 --> 07:54.400
Oh, I just love that word.
I love any city with a Corniche.

07:54.433 --> 07:56.500
It's such a beautiful word.

08:04.833 --> 08:07.133
The food of Oman
is a mix of flavors

08:07.167 --> 08:09.433
and ingredients and tastes
from Arabia

08:09.467 --> 08:13.200
and from all over
Oman's former empire.

08:13.233 --> 08:15.267
Bait Al Luban
is an old boarding house

08:15.300 --> 08:16.633
turned restaurant, where you can

08:16.667 --> 08:19.467
try dishes like pakora
and kachori...

08:19.500 --> 08:21.733
Which both
came back from India...

08:21.767 --> 08:23.567
Chapati, from East Africa,

08:23.600 --> 08:27.933
and shuwa, Oman's classic
special event dish.

08:27.967 --> 08:31.667
They do one version or another
of this all over the world.

08:31.700 --> 08:33.366
But shuwa is special.

08:33.400 --> 08:35.667
They slather a goat
with a spicy paste

08:35.700 --> 08:39.033
consisting of cumin,
coriander, red pepper,

08:39.067 --> 08:40.732
cinnamon, cardamom, and nutmeg.

08:40.767 --> 08:44.467
Then wrap the meat in palm
or banana leaves,

08:44.500 --> 08:47.233
dig a hole,

08:47.267 --> 08:49.833
throw in some meat,

08:49.867 --> 08:51.600
cover it up,

08:51.633 --> 08:53.867
and leave underground
for a day or two

08:53.900 --> 08:56.467
over hot coals.

08:56.500 --> 08:59.167
Oman has changed
in a way that's unique

08:59.200 --> 09:00.433
to anywhere I've been.

09:00.467 --> 09:02.033
I mean, I haven't seen any place

09:02.067 --> 09:05.300
that has sort of maintained

09:05.333 --> 09:07.667
the architecture
and the character

09:07.700 --> 09:08.667
that this country has.

09:08.700 --> 09:10.533
And that's
a really unusual thing.

09:10.567 --> 09:12.733
That's Omani...
The only country, I think

09:12.767 --> 09:16.400
of the Gulf region that kept
their tradition.

09:16.433 --> 09:17.900
And if you travel
outside Muscat,

09:17.933 --> 09:21.967
you see the flavor of
the old life still there.

09:22.000 --> 09:24.733
