09:24.767 --> 09:27.733
Hassan Meer is one of Oman's
preeminent fine artists,

09:27.767 --> 09:30.900
who works in painting
and photography.

09:30.933 --> 09:34.800
Muzna Almusafer is a filmmaker,
artist, and provocateur,

09:34.833 --> 09:37.667
representing the increasingly
vocal point of view

09:37.700 --> 09:41.367
of young Omani women in
the Middle Eastern art scene.

09:41.400 --> 09:44.600
I think in Arabia, we have
a tradition of storytelling

09:44.633 --> 09:48.767
and saying things
without saying them directly.

09:48.800 --> 09:50.767
They took this from poetry.

09:50.800 --> 09:53.500
They have a certain language
with a lot of tact,

09:53.533 --> 09:55.067
with a lot of...
Subtext.

09:55.100 --> 09:57.933
- Yeah.
- There's an unusual mix here.

09:57.967 --> 10:01.967
Very graceful, very proud mix
of cultures and languages.

10:02.000 --> 10:06.167
I mean, the mix was existent
from the beginning.

10:06.200 --> 10:08.200
There is a beauty
in being different

10:08.233 --> 10:10.600
and understanding the other.

10:10.633 --> 10:13.167
Such a difficult time
to make that argument.

10:13.200 --> 10:14.867
The whole world seems
to be going

10:14.900 --> 10:16.333
in exactly the opposite
direction.

10:16.367 --> 10:18.967
I mean, my country,
the last thing anyone

10:19.000 --> 10:24.000
seems to wanna do
is highlight the other.

10:24.033 --> 10:27.767
I think people discuss, like,
fears of multiculturalism.

10:27.800 --> 10:31.267
But within Oman, because of
our seafaring history,

10:31.300 --> 10:33.867
it's a traditional reality.

10:33.900 --> 10:36.067
It's our background.
It's who we are.

